  "texts": [
    "We correct for this effect by including a publisher-level analysis in Section 7.1 2.",
    "The training data is heterogeneous enough for the models to learn generalization across publishers.",
    "We test for this in Section 7.2",
    "Since it is conceivable that different publishers prefer particular topics, we compute a correlation between the produced test sets.",
    "While we find a small but consistent overlap between the 'Publisher' and 'Topic' test sets, we do not believe this alone accounts for the similarity in performance (see Appendix C.2)."
